
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `foo2xqx-wrapper` yek vasete (wrapper) baraye drajvar haye printere `foo2xqx` ast.  In dastoor be shoma komak mikonad ta ba printer haye ghadimi (legacy) ke az in drajver estefade mikonand, az tarigh ghabliat haye jadidtar e chap (printing) dar UNIX/Linux mesle CUPS estefade konid.  Be zaban sade, in yek tabdil konandeh ast baraye chap kardane chapaee ke printere shoma mifahmad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `--help`  --> ❓ Namayeshe rahnamaye dastoor va gozine-ha.
    🔹 `-z<level>` --> 🗜️  Sathe fishorde sazi (compression level). `0` yani hich fishordegi va `9` yani bishtarin sathe fishordegi.  Be tor mamool, az in gozine estefade nemishavad magar dar halat haye khass.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ foo2xqx-wrapper

    🔹 Dar aksar mavaghe, in dastoor be tor mostaghim az tarighe systeme chap (mesle CUPS) seda zade mishavad va niazi nist shoma an ra mostaghiman ejra konid.

    $ foo2xqx-wrapper --help

    🔹 Namayeshe rahnamaye dastoor.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    Agar systeme chape shoma (CUPS) printere shoma ra be dorosti shenasaee nemikonad, shoma mitavanid drajvare `foo2xqx` ra dastooran nasb konid va `foo2xqx-wrapper` be CUPS komak mikonad ta ba printere shoma ertebat bargharar konad.  In vasete (wrapper) file-haye chap ra be format monaseb baraye printere shoma tabdil mikonad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `foo2xqx-wrapper` command is a wrapper for the `foo2xqx` printer drivers. It allows you to use older (legacy) printers that use these drivers with newer printing systems in UNIX/Linux, such as CUPS. In simple terms, it's a translator for printing jobs that your printer understands.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `--help`  --> ❓ Display command help and options.
    🔹 `-z<level>` --> 🗜️ Compression level. `0` means no compression, and `9` means the highest level of compression.  This option is usually not used unless in specific circumstances.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ foo2xqx-wrapper

    🔹 In most cases, this command is called directly by the printing system (like CUPS) and does not need to be executed directly by you.

    $ foo2xqx-wrapper --help

    🔹 Display the command help.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    If your printing system (CUPS) is not correctly recognizing your printer, you can manually install the `foo2xqx` driver, and `foo2xqx-wrapper` helps CUPS communicate with your printer. This wrapper converts print files into a format suitable for your printer.
